did.abstract: Record Series 679 contains the administrative records of Chancellor Albert Carnesale (1997-2006). Records include congratulatory memorabilia and a Seoul National University scrapbook.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: COLLECTION STORED OFF-SITE AT SRLF: Open for research. Advance notice required for access. Contact the UCLA Library Special Collections Reference Desk for paging information.

userestrict.head: Publication Rights
userestrict.p: Copyright of portions of this collection has been assigned to The Regents of the University of California. The UCLA University Archives can grant permission to publish for materials to which it holds the copyright. All requests for permission to publish or quote must be submitted in writing to the UCLA University Archivist.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: We are committed to providing ethical, inclusive, and anti-racist description of the materials we steward, and to remediating existing description of our materials that contains language that may be offensive or cause harm. We invite you to submit feedback about how our collections are described, and how they could be described more accurately, by filling out the form located on our website: Report Potentially Offensive Description in Library Special Collections.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [Identification of item], Office of the Chancellor. Administrative files of Albert Carnesale (University Archives Record Series 679). UCLA Library Special Collections, University Archives.

bioghist.head: Biographical note
bioghist.p: Albert Carnesale is Chancellor Emeritus and Professor at the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA). He was Chancellor of the University from July 1, 1997 through June 30, 2006, and now serves as Professor of Public Policy and of Mechanical and Aerospace Engineering.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Record Series 679 contains the administrative records of Chancellor Albert Carnesale (1997-2006). Records include congratulatory memorabilia and a Seoul National University scrapbook.
This is an active record series; additional University records are expected to be added.
